Former Internal Security assistant minister Alfred Khang&rsquo;ati has denied claims on social media that he has bowed out of the Bungoma governor race.Speaking to journalists in Bungoma town on Wednesday, he also denied backing Ford Kenya candidate Wycliffe Wangamati for the top job.Rumours have been spreading in WhatsApp groups and Facebook that Wangamati gave Khangati cash to back him in the race.Khangati said he will run on the ODM ticket. &lsquo;&rsquo;I have heard very funny reports and talk in town and on social media. Those are mere rumors and propaganda,&rsquo;&rsquo; he said.Khang&rsquo;ati said he met Wangamati in Webuye town last week to discuss how to work together to ensure incumbent Kenneth Lusaka does not win. He said residents urged him to run.